<codeBook xmlns="ddi:codebook:2_5" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="ddi:codebook:2_5 https://ddialliance.org/Specification/DDI-Codebook/2.5/XMLSchema/codebook.xsd" version="2.5"><docDscr><citation><titlStmt><titl>Microcensus 2001, 2. quarter: Extended Housing Survey, Duration and Structure of Working Time (SUF edition)</titl><IDNo agency="DOI">doi:10.11587/ZK4QEX</IDNo></titlStmt><distStmt><distrbtr source="archive">AUSSDA</distrbtr><distDate>2020-06-24</distDate></distStmt><verStmt source="archive"><version date="2026-01-13" type="RELEASED">2</version></verStmt><biblCit>Statistics Austria, 2020, "Microcensus 2001, 2. quarter: Extended Housing Survey, Duration and Structure of Working Time (SUF edition)", https://doi.org/10.11587/ZK4QEX, AUSSDA, V2, UNF:6:qjX1PnFTV+ud6PIYXSXtcw== [fileUNF]</biblCit></citation></docDscr><stdyDscr><citation><titlStmt><titl>Microcensus 2001, 2. quarter: Extended Housing Survey, Duration and Structure of Working Time (SUF edition)</titl><IDNo agency="DOI">doi:10.11587/ZK4QEX</IDNo><IDNo agency="WISDOM number">MZ2001_2</IDNo></titlStmt><rspStmt><AuthEnty affiliation="Statistik Austria">Statistics Austria</AuthEnty><othId role="Data Collector">Statistics Austria</othId></rspStmt><prodStmt/><distStmt><distrbtr source="archive">AUSSDA</distrbtr><distrbtr>The Austrian Social Science Data Archive</distrbtr><contact affiliation="The Austrian Social Science Data Archive" email="info@aussda.at">AUSSDA</contact><depositr>Statistics Austria</depositr></distStmt><serStmt><serName>Microcensus</serName><serInfo>The microcensus has been carried out since the 1970s and has been repeatedly adapted to changing circumstances over time. The last major reform took place in 2014.</serInfo></serStmt><holdings URI="https://doi.org/10.11587/ZK4QEX"/></citation><stdyInfo><subject><keyword xml:lang="en">Social Sciences</keyword><keyword vocab="ELSST" vocabURI="https://elsst.cessda.eu/id">Energy consumption</keyword><keyword vocab="ELSST" vocabURI="https://elsst.cessda.eu/id">Hours of work</keyword><keyword vocab="ELSST" vocabURI="https://elsst.cessda.eu/id">Arrangement of working time</keyword><keyword vocab="ELSST" vocabURI="https://elsst.cessda.eu/id">Demography</keyword><keyword vocab="ELSST" vocabURI="https://elsst.cessda.eu/id">Employment</keyword><keyword vocab="ELSST" vocabURI="https://elsst.cessda.eu/id">Housing conditions</keyword><topcClas vocab="CESSDA Topic Classification" vocabURI="https://vocabularies.cessda.eu/vocabulary/TopicClassification">Housing</topcClas><topcClas vocab="CESSDA Topic Classification" vocabURI="https://vocabularies.cessda.eu/vocabulary/TopicClassification">Labour and employment</topcClas></subject><abstract>Full edition for scientific use. According to the regulation No. 1578/2000 by the European Commission from 19th July 2000, member states have to conduct a sample survey on the ad-hoc module „Duration and Structure of Working Time”. The European Commission needs structural statistics on flexible working hour regulations and types of labour force to monitor employment policy guidelines. Austria follows this regulation by conduction this sample survey as a Microcensus special survey in June 2001. These types of working hour regulations and labour contracts are the focal point of the survey: 1. false self-employment (questions B28-B30) 2. extra hours (questions B31-B32) 3. shift-work (questions B33-B35) 4. new flexible working hour models (questions B36-B41). The „Extended Housing Survey” includes questions on energy use and car parking space.</abstract><sumDscr><collDate cycle="P1" event="start" date="2001-04">2001-04</collDate><collDate cycle="P1" event="end" date="2001-06">2001-06</collDate><nation>Austria</nation><anlyUnit>Household</anlyUnit><universe>Persons registered in the central register of residents living in private households</universe><dataKind>Numeric</dataKind></sumDscr><notes>&lt;p>To access the data, please download the &lt;a href="https://aussda.at/fileadmin/user_upload/p_aussda/Documents/AUSSDA_Nutzungsvereinbarung_Mikrozensus.pdf">Terms of Use Agreement&lt;/a> for Microcensus Data by Statistics Austria, sign it and send it to &lt;a href="mailto:info@aussda.at">info@aussda.at&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></notes></stdyInfo><method><dataColl><timeMeth>Longitudinal: Trend/Repeated cross-section</timeMeth><sampProc>Probability: Stratified: Disproportional</sampProc><collMode>Face-to-face interview</collMode><resInstru>Structured questionnaire</resInstru><sources><dataSrc>Population group</dataSrc></sources></dataColl><notes type="Additional Information on Sampling:">The basis for the selection is the houses- and apartment census from 1991 and the ongoing housing-statistic in a one-level selection process for Vienna and Vorarlberg. Otherwise, it is a two-level selection process (first a selection of municipalities and then samples of houses and apartments)</notes><anlyInfo/></method><dataAccs><setAvail/><useStmt/><notes type="DVN:TOA" level="dv">To access the files, users need to log in and click on "Request Access". AUSSDA will then contact you for more information.</notes><notes type="DVN:TOU" level="dv">&lt;a href="https://aussda.at/en/terms-of-use-agreement-for-the-microcensus-lfs-by-statistics-austria">Terms of use agreement for Microcensus LFS data by Statistics Austria&lt;/a></notes></dataAccs><othrStdyMat/></stdyDscr><fileDscr ID="f7759" URI="https://data.aussda.at/api/access/datafile/7759"><fileTxt><fileName>10247_da01_de_v1_0.tab</fileName><dimensns><caseQnty>67584</caseQnty><varQnty>165</varQnty></dimensns><fileType>text/tab-separated-values</fileType></fileTxt><notes level="file" type="VDC:UNF" subject="Universal Numeric Fingerprint">UNF:6:0rlCO5xUQ4NrrhjVQdPEWQ==</notes><notes level="file" type="DATAVERSE:FILEDESC" subject="DataFile Description">Core data file "Extended Housing Survey", not imputed data - STATA format - 165 Variables, 67584 Observations
